Class GraphHelper

  • Object
    • GraphHelper

  • public class GraphHelper
extends Object
    A helper used in generated script to manipulate the graph efficiently and avoid complex instruction creation.

    Gwendal DANIEL

      • createElement

        public Vertex createElement(Vertex source,
                            String targetLabel,
                            Vertex metaclassVertex)
        Creates a new element Vertex and connects it to its metaclass. A trace link is also generated between the source element and the created one to ensure transformation consistency
        Parameters:
        source - the Vertex that triggered the element creation (i.e. the source element in the transformation)
        targetLabel - the label of the created element in the transformation (i.e. the name in the binding)
        metaclassVertex - the Vertex representing the metaclass
        Returns:
        the created Vertex

      • resolveProxies

        public void resolveProxies(Vertex source,
                           Vertex target)
        Resolve the proxy links connected to source by setting their tail to target. Proxy links are removed from the graph, and resolved Edge are created using target
        Parameters:

        target - the Vertex that resolves the proxies

      • linkReference

        public Edge linkReference(Vertex source,
                          Vertex target,
                          String label)
        Links two elements by creating an edge between the corresponding Vertex. Note that target is an element in the source model that has to be resolved. If target cannot be resolved (because the corresponding Vertex has not been created yet) a proxy link (see @link{GraphHelper#pLink(Vertex, Vertex, String)}) is created that will be resolved later.
        Parameters:
        source - the tail of the link
        target - a source element that is resolved and set as the head of the link. If it cannot be resolved a proxy link is created instead
        label - the label of the link
        Returns:
        the created Edge

      • linkReference

        public List<Edge> linkReference(Vertex source,
                                GremlinGroovyPipeline<?,Vertex> target,
                                String label)
        Links all the elements of target to source by creating edges between the corresponding Vertex. Note that target are elements in the source model that have to be resolved. If target elements cannot be resolved (because corresponding Vertex have not been created yet) a proxy link {see GraphHelper#pLink(Vertex, Vertex, String)} is created that will be resolved later.
        Parameters:
        source - the tail of the links
        target - a GremlinGroovyPipeline containing the elements that have to be resolved and set as the head of the created links. If some of them cannot be resolved a proxy link is created instead
        label - the label of the link
        Returns:
        a list containing the created Edges
